<section class="block-section do">
  <span class="section-tag">🛠️ Do</span>
  <h2>Today's work — choose one path</h2>
  <p class="sub">All four paths end with a working draft of the plan. The path is about where you spend the block.</p>
  <div class="choice-intro">
    <strong>Learning Intention:</strong> I have a working draft of all four core sections of my plan, with implementation recommendations addressed to a named municipal body.
  </div>
  <div class="choice-board">
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">A</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Draft all four core sections (default)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Work straight through: area profile, allocation, trade-off analysis, and at least five implementation recommendations. Get a complete rough version down, then tighten. A complete weak draft beats a polished fragment.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Default</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">B</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Recommendations specificity pass (stretch)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">If your draft is mostly done, go through every recommendation and make it specific: what exactly, who acts, by when, and what it costs in money or equity. Strike any that are really just wishes. This is the move that lifts T/T.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Stretch</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">C</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Partner stress-test the weak section (choice)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Take the section that is fighting you to whichever <a href="/ai-partners/urban-planner/">partner</a> is most likely to attack it. Revise until it survives the challenge. Document the exchange and the one thing the partner got wrong.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Choice</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">D</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Peer-help on your weakest section (practice)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Bring the section you are least sure about to the peer-help table. Trade drafts with a partner: each of you names the one thing that would most improve the other's weak section, then fix yours.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Pairs · Practice</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

